This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it focuses on improving the expressiveness of deep learning frameworks. It may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with neural networks and their implementation. Additionally, it may be relevant to cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as recursive neural networks have been used in natural language processing and image recognition tasks.
